  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Money laundering legal approaches vary significantly across different countries, but I'll provide an overview of some key comparative perspectives:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Comprehensive Bank Secrecy Act\n- Strict reporting requirements\n- Aggressive criminal prosecution\n- Focus on financial institution compliance\n- Significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Unified Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Centralized regulatory framework\n- Enhanced customer due diligence\n- Emphasis on transparency\n- Cross-border cooperation mechanisms\n\n3. United Kingdom Model\n- Sophisticated financial crime legislation\n- Strong international collaboration\n- Sophisticated risk-based assessment\n- Significant regulatory oversight\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n\n4. Swiss Approach\n- Traditional banking secrecy laws\n- Gradual reduction of banking confidentiality\n- Increasing international cooperation\n- Balanced regulatory environment\n\n5. Developing Nations\n- Often less sophisticated legal frameworks\n- Weaker enforcement capabilities\n- Emerging regulatory structures\n- Higher vulnerability to financial crimes\n\nCommon elements across approaches:\n- Customer identification requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- International information sharing\n- Criminal penalties\n- Financial institution obligations\n\nWould you be interested in more detailed analysis of specific jurisdictional approaches?",
